comment: Lopez (NYK) sets the screen on Bazemore (ATL) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
All Technical Fouls are reviewed by Basketball Operations and the League Office.
Prior to the simultaneous possession between Porzingis (NYK) and Bazemore (ATL), Korver (ATL) grabs Porzingis' arm and affects his shot attempt.
Lopez (NYK) sets the screen on Millsap (ATL) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
RATR shows that Horford (ATL) maintains legal guarding position and cleanly knocks the ball away from Anthony (NYK).
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that the ball was last touched by Anthony (NYK) was overturned. New York retained possession.
Korver (ATL) maintains a legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Porzingis (NYK) that does not affect his RSBQ at the start of the drive.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that the ball was last touched by Millsap (ATL) was overturned. Atlanta was awarded possession.
Afflalo (NYK) hand checks Schroder (ATL) and affects his RSBQ on the baseline drive.
Schroder (ATL), the shooter, enters the lane prior to the ball making contact with the rim.
Afflalo (NYK) grabs Schroder (ATL) by the shoulder and makes contact with his body that causes both players to fall to the ground and affects his ability to retrieve the rebound.
Horford (ATL) commits a take foul on Anthony (NYK).
